Same as https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/108369, but with much simpler API (only adding two functions).

<details>
  <summary>A quick description of the issue this PR is fixing</summary>

- we can't predict how glyphs are distributed among textures and used, so batching was constantly breaking.
- font glyphs are designed to overlay and in general draw order does not matter.

For example, the following string "ABCDEFAAEDBF" might be processed in this way (assuming every texture can hold 4 glyphs, so simplicity, in practice this is only relevant for the text with a lot of distinct characters):
- A → glyph is encountered for the first time and rasterized to texture 1, and drawn
- B → same, and drawn
- C → same, and drawn
- D → same, and drawn
- E → texture 1 is full, glyph is rasterized to texture 2, and drawn (batching breaks since texture is changed)
- F → same, and drawn

| Texture 1 | Texture 2 |
|---|---|
| ABCD | EF |

- A → batching breaks
- A
- E → batching breaks
- D → batching breaks
- B
- F → batching breaks

This PR rearranges draw commands to ensure batching won't unnecessarily break.

```c++
// Line 1:
RenderingServer::get_singleton()->canvas_item_set_presort_level(ci, 0);
// draw A outline from texture 1
// draw B outline from texture 2
// draw C outline from texture 1
RenderingServer::get_singleton()->canvas_item_set_presort_level(ci, 1);
// draw A text from texture 3
// draw B text from texture 4
// draw C text from texture 3

// Line 2:
RenderingServer::get_singleton()->canvas_item_set_presort_level(ci, 0);
// draw D outline from texture 2
// draw C outline from texture 1
RenderingServer::get_singleton()->canvas_item_set_presort_level(ci, 1);
// draw D text from texture 4
// draw C text from texture 3

RenderingServer::get_singleton()->canvas_item_flush_presort(ci); // rearanges draw commands ignoring original call order.

// Rearranged as (4 batches instead of 10):
// draw A outline from texture 1
// draw C outline from texture 1
// draw C outline from texture 1
// draw B outline from texture 2
// draw D outline from texture 2
// draw A text from texture 3
// draw C text from texture 3
// draw C text from texture 3
// draw B text from texture 4
// draw D text from texture 4
```

</details>

