I did some adjustments in `AHashMap` which seemed to have increased performance in some situations.

### Removed the `_elements` check from `_lookup_idx_with_hash()`
There is already a validity check of `_elements` in `_lookup_idx()`, so by having it in `lookup_idx_with_hash()` too means double check.

This affects every function of `AHashMap` that uses `_lookup_idx()`: `get()`, `getptr()`, `has()`, `erase()`, `replace_key()`, `find()`, `const &operator[]` and `get_index()`.

Checks were added where `_lookup_idx_with_hash()` are called outside `_lookup_idx()`.

Consequently, this makes most `AHashMap` lookup calls in pair with `HashMap`. `_lookup_idx_with_hash()` pretty much becomes `AHashMap`'s version of `HashMap::_lookup_idx_unchecked()`.

### Removed the `unlikely` conditions from `AHashMap` lookups.
Simply because the benchmarks below over the change above on my end showed it was slightly faster.

### More versions of `_lookup_idx()` to remove the need of declaring a meta index
Some meta index declarations exist for the sole purpose of providing a value for `_lookup_idx()` to handle.

On my end, duplicating code to avoid handling a meta index resulted in faster execution.

