This PR extends the `ResourceLoader` by 4 public methods for retrieval of either all or only filtered "cached" resource paths as arrays or dictionaries in C++, GDScript and C#

**Note(s)** 
A Resource is considered cached when **all of the following conditions are true**:
- It must have a `get_reference_count() > 0` (assigned to exported variables via inspector or assigned to any variable via code)
- It must have a valid `resource_path` set (Examples: `res://icon.svg` or `C:/path/to/my/file.png` )

