Added a new `sort_by_key` method on `Array` that takes a `Callable` argument to generate a key for each item in the array, then sorts by these key values.

Closes https://github.com/godotengine/godot-proposals/issues/11477 (and maybe https://github.com/godotengine/godot-proposals/issues/5552 - the interface used here is different than discussed in that proposal, but this does provide a stable sort)

The new `sort_by_key` method has a few benefits over using `sort_custom`:
- `sort_custom`'s `Callable` argument must be called for each comparison done in the sort, resulting in O(nlogn) calls.  For `sort_by_key`, the `Callable` is only called once per item, then all sorting is done within C++ code.  Due to the overhead of calling into gdscript functions, this makes `sort_by_key` significantly faster than `sort_custom`, around 3-10x faster depending on size of array and `Callable` used.
- `sort_by_key` is a stable sort.  Since the keys need to be linked back to the original `Variant` (currently done by storing the index with the key), `_ArrayVariantKeySort` has enough information to keep the original ordering of equal items.
- Slightly simpler to call - this might just be my own preference, but for cases when the same property is being compared between two items in the array, half of `sort_custom`'s lambda argument is basically just duplicating the same field/method call for each item.  `sort_by_key` feels more direct/concise, only specifying the field to sort by once.

I think the main downside/trade-off is that `sort_by_key` uses a separate array to store the keys while sorting, so it does require more memory than `sort_custom`.

I have another PR open at https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/96014 that focuses on just adding stable versions of existing sort methods.  I think this PR should probably replace that one - I don't think there's much value in more stable sorting methods if `sort_by_key` is added, but leaving both open for now.

Compared with gdscript below:

```gdscript
func _ready() -> void:
	run_test("sort_custom_small")
	run_test("sort_by_key_small")
	run_test("sort_custom_large")
	run_test("sort_by_key_large")
	run_test("sort_custom_obj")
	run_test("sort_custom_obj_fast")
	run_test("sort_by_key_obj")

func get_array(size: int):
	var arr: Array
	for i in size:
		arr.push_back(Vector3(i, i*2, i*3))
	return arr

func get_obj_array(size: int):
	var arr: Array
	for i in size:
		var node2D = Node2D.new()
		node2D.position.x = i % 10
		node2D.position.y = i / 10
		arr.push_back(node2D)
	return arr

func run_test(test_name: String):
	var start := Time.get_ticks_msec()
	call(test_name)
	var end := Time.get_ticks_msec()
	print("%s: %dms" % [test_name.rpad(21), end - start])

func sort_custom_small():
	var arr = get_array(20)
	for i in 100000:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_custom(func(a: Vector3, b: Vector3): return a.length() < b.length())

func sort_by_key_small():
	var arr = get_array(20)
	for i in 100000:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_by_key(func(v: Vector3): return v.length())
		
func sort_custom_large():
	var arr = get_array(100000)
	for i in 10:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_custom(func(a: Vector3, b: Vector3): return a.length() < b.length())

func sort_by_key_large():
	var arr = get_array(100000)
	for i in 10:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_by_key(func(v: Vector3): return v.length())

func sort_custom_obj():
	var arr = get_obj_array(1000)
	for i in 1000:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_custom(func(a: Node2D, b: Node2D):
			return [a.position.y, a.position.x] < [b.position.y, b.position.x]
		)

func sort_custom_obj_fast():
	var arr = get_obj_array(1000)
	for i in 1000:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_custom(func(a: Node2D, b: Node2D):
			if a.position.y < b.position.y:
				return true
			if a.position.y > b.position.y:
				return false
			return a.position.x < b.position.x
		)

func sort_by_key_obj():
	var arr = get_obj_array(1000)
	for i in 1000:
		arr.shuffle()
		arr.sort_by_key(func(n: Node2D): return [n.position.y, n.position.x])
```

